description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM/SECONDMENT FOR 15 MONTHS DUE TO THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN APPLYING FOR THE SECONDMENT POSITION, YOU MUST OBTAIN PERMISSION FROM YOUR CURRENT LINE MANAGER PRIOR TO APPLYING FOR THIS POST.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Care Development Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Passionate about Primary and Community Services and looking for a new opportunity?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Betsi Cadwaladr University Health Board’s, Primary &amp; Community Care Academy are looking for a Primary Care Development Manager to join the team on a 15 month contract (secondment or fixed term), to cover maternity leave.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an individual who has experience of working on service development projects, and has knowledge of Primary Care services in north Wales.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will be able to understand and promote the strategic direction for Primary Care and Community Care services within the Health Board and with external stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively contributing the design and delivery of services at a local level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure that effective communications are maintained within the department, and relevant stakeholders, updating all on any relevant project issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educated to degree level / equivalent level of work experience and knowledge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project management experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Primary Care Experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of managing social media presence and development of online tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work on own initiative and organise / prioritise own &amp; team workload.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For full list of essential criteria please see the Job Description &amp; Personal Specification&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead on the implementation and of the Primary Care Recruitment Strategy for North Wales.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting Practices with Recruitment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing a specific service development project, including eConsult and areas of the Advanced Practice Paramedic Pacesetter project.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead on social media pages for the Academy (Facebook &amp; Twitter).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead on the content for the Academy website.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please see the Job Description &amp; Personal Specification&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Location:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The based for this role is negotiable, with the option of working from home during Covid-19.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Primary &amp; Community Care Academy is currently based in Llandudno General Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Should You Apply?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to be part of a team who is passionate about delivering high quality projects and outcomes for Primary Care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Your working hours can be flexible between the hours of 8:00am – 6pm Monday to Friday.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 15th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gemma Nosworthy (Primary &amp; Community Care Academy Manager) Gemma.Nosworthy@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
